<item>
            <title>[LU-18987] Strange LASSERT in mdt_dom_read_on_open()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18987</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a strange code in mdt_dom_read_on_open (highlighted by smatch) that asserts for some non-sensical stuff that&apos;s not even changed inside the loop:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;rc = dt_read_prep(env, mo, lnb, nr_local);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (unlikely(rc))
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; GOTO(buf_put, rc);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* copy data to the buffer &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;finally&lt;/span&gt; */&lt;/span&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (i = 0; i &amp;lt; nr_local; i++) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; *p = kmap(lnb[i].lnb_page);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; off;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; LASSERT(lnb[i].lnb_page_offset == 0);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; off = lnb[i].lnb_len &amp;amp; ~PAGE_MASK;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (off &amp;gt; 0)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; memset(p + off, 0, PAGE_SIZE - off);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; memcpy(buf + (i &amp;lt;&amp;lt; PAGE_SHIFT), p, lnb[i].lnb_len);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; kunmap(lnb[i].lnb_page);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; copied += lnb[i].lnb_len;
====&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; LASSERT(rc &amp;lt;= len);        &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;======= here
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I checked with Mike (original path author) and he thinks we can just safely drop it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
